ere \"Come Lord Jesus, come quickly!\" The letter was published in the Rawson Family Memorial. Cotton Mather quoted it in the sermon he preached at Rawson's funeral."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Her gravestone names her father, not husband","body":"Her gravestone in Mendon reads: \"Here lies inter'd ye Remains of Mrs. Susanna Rawson, Relict of ye late Rev. Mr. Grindal Rawson... and daughter to ye Rev. Mr. John Wilson 1st Minister of ye Gospel in Medfield.\" She outlived her husband by 33 years, dying July 8, 1748, age 83."},{"number":3,"category":"legacy","header":"Ancestor of President Taft through both Taft brothers","body":"Her granddaughter Mary Dorr Taft married Moses Taft, and her great-granddaughter Rhoda Rawson Taft married Aaron Taft — Moses's and Aaron's fathers were brothers. President William Howard Taft descends through the Aaron Taft line."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"in_law","related_id":"X00009","display_label":"was her father-in-law, the Bay Colony’s secretary","link_text":"Edward Rawson"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Susanna Wilson Rawson","first_name":"Susanna","last_name":"Rawson","married_names":["Rawson"],"maiden_name":"Wilson"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"former_ids":[],"education":[],"career":[],"is_placeholder":false,"slug":"susanna-rawson-1664"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM001","name":"Old Cemetery","city":"Mendon","state":"Massachusetts","address":"35 Main Street","zip":"01756","gps":{"latitude":42.10377,"longitude":-71.54912},"founded":1669,"visitable":true,"notes":"Contains graves of 40 Revolutionary War soldiers. Massachusetts Historical Commission MACRIS MEN803.","hooker_connections":["H00026","H00081","H00365","H00366","H00369","H00373","H00865","H00869","H00877","H00882","H00883","H00897","H00903","I00005","I00126","I00145","X00455","X00469","X00478","I00111","